      "role": "user",
      "content": "log transformation makes sense. i'll try that. but i'm also seeing some really weird extreme outliers in the residuals, like some values are way higher than anything else in the set. should i just delete those or is there a more formal way to deal with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Deleting outliers is tempting, but you must be careful, as you might be throwing away valuable information, which is almost as bad as leaving a poorly-formed data structure. A formal way to deal with extreme outliers in residuals is to use robust regression techniques, or perhaps Winsorization. Winsorization is a good middle ground; instead of outright deleting the data points, you cap the extreme values at a certain percentile. This keeps the data in, but it tames the wild swings.",
      "source": "target",
